{
  "name": "Divine Intervention",
  "_id": "matClrDivineInte",
  "type": "feat",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You can call on your deity or pantheon to intervene on your behalf. As a Magic action, you can choose either <strong>Extend Magic</strong> or <strong>Beseech Divinity</strong> for its effect.</p><p><strong>Extend Magic.</strong> Choose any @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.rules.JournalEntry.iP1dkRR5XjXBzGp6]{Cleric spell} of level 5 or lower that doesn't require a Reaction to cast. As part of the same action, you cast that spell without expending a spell slot or needing Material components. You can't use this feature again until you finish a Long Rest.</p><p><strong>Beseech Divinity.</strong> Describe the assistance you seek, and roll percentile dice. If you roll a number equal to or lower than your cleric level plus your Wisdom modifier (minimum of 0), your deity intervenes. Your DM chooses the effect.</p><p>If your deity intervenes, you cannot use the <strong>Beseech Divinity </strong>feature again for 7 days. Otherwise, you can use it again after you finish a long rest.</p><section class=\"secret\" id=\"secret-LP7yqqobTjOqeswv\"><p><strong>Foundry Note</strong></p><p>Uncheck the \"Consumption\" box when casting the spell for the free use. This feature can be used to track available uses.</p></section>",
